  "response": "I'm sorry, but the claim that Jawaharlal Nehru was a Muslim is not supported by historical evidence. Jawaharlal Nehru, the first Prime Minister of India, was born into a prominent Hindu family. His father, Motilal Nehru, was a well-known lawyer and a leader in the Indian National Congress, and his family adhered to Hindu traditions.\n\nNehru was known for his secular beliefs and his commitment to fostering a diverse and inclusive India, where people of all religions could coexist peacefully. While he respected and promoted religious pluralism, his personal religious background was Hindu.\n\nIf you have come across sources making this claim, it's important to verify their credibility and consult reputable historical records or scholarly works on Jawaharlal Nehru's life and legacy.",
